162
00:07:50,526 --> 00:07:51,610
Scott: I just kind of coasted home.

163
00:07:52,430 --> 00:07:56,284
Rym: I probably would have just, as I crested the hill, downshifted.

164
00:07:56,786 --> 00:08:00,770
Scott: Yeah, either way, I'm just saying, I had no problems going home at all.

165
00:08:00,990 --> 00:08:07,340
Rym: It seems to me that people, when it comes to snow, when they're driving, can't take a rational, middle-of-the-ground approach.

166
00:08:07,942 --> 00:08:18,269
Rym: It seems like everyone out there either goes faster for some reason, just as fast as they can possibly go, tailgating me, or they go five miles an hour.

167
00:08:19,451 --> 00:08:24,027
Scott: It's like people are either driving, you know, they're like, "Oh, it's safe to drive," and they drive fast.

168
00:08:24,429 --> 00:08:26,797
Scott: Or they go, "Oh, it's dangerous," and they drive too slow.

169
00:08:26,817 --> 00:08:27,900
Rym: It's like, what the fuck?

170
00:08:28,061 --> 00:08:31,634
Rym: I mean, first, I pass all these horrible accidents, and now I'm just on the taconic.

171
00:08:31,674 --> 00:08:33,361
